---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Token Dense Dialect (TDD) — LeanCTX"
  description="TDD replaces verbose prose with symbolic notation. Maximize meaning per token — no articles, no filler, no pleasantries. 8-25% fewer tokens with minimal information loss."
  breadcrumbs={[
    { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
    { name: 'Protocols', url: '/protocols' },
    { name: 'TDD', url: '/protocols/tdd' },
  ]}
>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
     HERO
     ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="section-y">
  <div class="content-grid">
    <div class="animate-entrance">
      <p class="fluid-label text-muted" style="margin-bottom: clamp(1.25rem, 1rem + 1vw, 2.5rem);">
        Protocols / TDD
      </p>
    </div>

    <h1 class="font-display fluid-h1 font-bold text-text-bright animate-entrance stagger-1" style="margin-bottom: clamp(1.5rem, 1rem + 1.5vw, 3rem);">
      Token Dense Dialect.
    </h1>

    <p class="fluid-body text-muted animate-entrance stagger-2" style="margin-bottom: clamp(2.5rem, 2rem + 2vw, 5rem); max-width: 44rem;">
      TDD replaces verbose prose with symbolic notation. Maximize meaning per token — no articles, no filler, no pleasantries. The AI communicates in a compact dialect that preserves all information with 8&#8211;25% fewer tokens.
    </p>

    <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center animate-entrance stagger-3" style="gap: clamp(0.75rem, 0.5rem + 0.5vw, 1.25rem);">
      <a href="/docs/getting-started" class="btn-primary inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg" style="padding: clamp(0.7rem, 0.55rem + 0.3vw, 0.9rem) clamp(1.5rem, 1rem + 0.75vw, 2.25rem); font-size: clamp(0.8125rem, 0.78rem + 0.15vw, 0.9375rem);">
        Get Started
        <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13 7l5 5m0 0l-5 5m5-5H6"/></svg>
      </a>
      <a href="/protocols" class="btn-outline inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg" style="padding: clamp(0.7rem, 0.55rem + 0.3vw, 0.9rem) clamp(1.5rem, 1rem + 0.75vw, 2.25rem); font-size: clamp(0.8125rem, 0.78rem + 0.15vw, 0.9375rem);">
        All Protocols
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="section-divider content-grid"></div>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
     WHY TDD EXISTS
     ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="section-y">
  <div class="content-grid">
    <p class="fluid-label text-muted animate-entrance" style="margin-bottom: clamp(1rem, 0.75rem + 0.5vw, 1.5rem);">
      The Problem
    </p>
    <h2 class="font-display fluid-h2 font-bold text-text-bright animate-entrance stagger-1" style="margin-bottom: clamp(1.25rem, 1rem + 0.5vw, 2rem);">
      Why TDD exists.
    </h2>
    <p class="text-muted fluid-body animate-entrance stagger-2" style="margin-bottom: clamp(3rem, 2rem + 3vw, 6rem); max-width: 44rem;">
      Information entropy per token is the key metric. Most AI responses are filled with tokens that carry nearly zero unique information.
    </p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 animate-entrance stagger-3" style="gap: clamp(1rem, 0.75rem + 0.75vw, 1.5rem);">
      <div class="tdd-insight-card card">
        <div class="tdd-insight-header tdd-insight-header--low">
          <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M18.364 18.364A9 9 0 005.636 5.636m12.728 12.728A9 9 0 015.636 5.636m12.728 12.728L5.636 5.636"/></svg>
          Low Entropy
        </div>
        <div class="tdd-insight-body font-mono" style="font-size: clamp(0.6875rem, 0.65rem + 0.1vw, 0.8125rem);">
          <div class="tdd-insight-line">
            <span class="text-text-bright">"function"</span> <span class="text-muted">uses 1 token</span>
          </div>
          <div class="tdd-insight-line">
            <span class="text-danger">Conveys nearly zero unique information</span>
          </div>
          <div class="tdd-insight-line">
            <span class="text-muted">The AI already knows it's a function from context</span>
          </div>
          <div class="tdd-insight-line">
            <span class="text-danger">Wastes budget on what's already implied</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tdd-insight-card card">
        <div class="tdd-insight-header tdd-insight-header--high">
          <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/></svg>
          High Entropy
        </div>
        <div class="tdd-insight-body font-mono" style="font-size: clamp(0.6875rem, 0.65rem + 0.1vw, 0.8125rem);">
          <div class="tdd-insight-line">
            <span class="text-accent-3">λ</span> <span class="text-muted">uses 1 token</span>
          </div>
          <div class="tdd-insight-line">
            <span class="text-accent">Conveys the same meaning in less space</span>
          </div>
          <div class="tdd-insight-line">
            <span class="text-muted">Frees token budget for actual logic and context</span>
          </div>
          <div class="tdd-insight-line">
            <span class="text-accent">Every token carries maximum signal</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="text-muted fluid-sm animate-entrance stagger-4" style="margin-top: clamp(1.5rem, 1rem + 1vw, 2.5rem); max-width: 44rem;">
      lean-ctx is a lossless minifier for human thought. TDD applies this principle to AI communication — stripping syntactic sugar while preserving every bit of semantic content.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="section-divider content-grid"></div>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
     SYMBOL TABLE
     ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="section-y">
  <div class="content-grid">
    <p class="fluid-label text-muted animate-entrance" style="margin-bottom: clamp(1rem, 0.75rem + 0.5vw, 1.5rem);">
      Reference
    </p>
    <h2 class="font-display fluid-h2 font-bold text-text-bright animate-entrance stagger-1" style="margin-bottom: clamp(1.25rem, 1rem + 0.5vw, 2rem);">
      Symbol table.
    </h2>
    <p class="text-muted fluid-body animate-entrance stagger-2" style="margin-bottom: clamp(3rem, 2rem + 3vw, 6rem); max-width: 44rem;">
      Each symbol replaces 1 token of prose with 1 token of dense notation. The AI learns these symbols from the system prompt and uses them consistently throughout the session.
    </p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 animate-entrance stagger-3" style="gap: clamp(1px, 0.1vw, 1px);">
      <div class="tdd-table-card card">
        <h3 class="tdd-table-heading">Structural</h3>
        <table class="tdd-symbol-table">
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td class="tdd-symbol text-accent-3">λ</td>
              <td class="tdd-meaning">function</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="tdd-symbol text-accent-3">§</td>
              <td class="tdd-meaning">module / struct</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="tdd-symbol text-accent-3">∂</td>
              <td class="tdd-meaning">interface / trait</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="tdd-symbol text-accent-3">τ</td>
              <td class="tdd-meaning">type</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="tdd-symbol text-accent-3">ε</td>
              <td class="tdd-meaning">enum</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="tdd-table-card card">
        <h3 class="tdd-table-heading">Actions</h3>
        <table class="tdd-symbol-table">
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td class="tdd-symbol text-accent-3">⊕</td>
              <td class="tdd-meaning">add</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="tdd-symbol text-accent-3">⊖</td>
              <td class="tdd-meaning">remove</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="tdd-symbol text-accent-3">∆</td>
              <td class="tdd-meaning">modify</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="tdd-symbol text-accent-3">→</td>
              <td class="tdd-meaning">returns</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="tdd-symbol text-accent-3">⇒</td>
              <td class="tdd-meaning">implies</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="tdd-table-card card">
        <h3 class="tdd-table-heading">Status</h3>
        <table class="tdd-symbol-table">
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td class="tdd-symbol text-accent">✓</td>
              <td class="tdd-meaning">ok</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="tdd-symbol text-danger">✗</td>
              <td class="tdd-meaning">fail</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="tdd-symbol text-accent-2">⚠</td>
              <td class="tdd-meaning">warning</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="section-divider content-grid"></div>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
     CHANGE NOTATION
     ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="section-y">
  <div class="content-grid">
    <p class="fluid-label text-muted animate-entrance" style="margin-bottom: clamp(1rem, 0.75rem + 0.5vw, 1.5rem);">
      Notation
    </p>
    <h2 class="font-display fluid-h2 font-bold text-text-bright animate-entrance stagger-1" style="margin-bottom: clamp(1.25rem, 1rem + 0.5vw, 2rem);">
      Change notation.
    </h2>
    <p class="text-muted fluid-body animate-entrance stagger-2" style="margin-bottom: clamp(3rem, 2rem + 3vw, 6rem); max-width: 44rem;">
      TDD defines a compact notation for describing code changes. Instead of verbose descriptions, the AI reports modifications as structured one-liners.
    </p>

    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 animate-entrance stagger-3" style="gap: clamp(1rem, 0.75rem + 0.75vw, 1.5rem);">
      <div class="terminal-chrome">
        <div class="terminal-header flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2.5">
          <span class="terminal-dot bg-[#ff5f57]"></span>
          <span class="terminal-dot bg-[#febc2e]"></span>
          <span class="terminal-dot bg-[#28c840]"></span>
          <span class="ml-3 text-xs text-muted font-mono">Change Notation</span>
        </div>
        <div class="terminal-body px-5 py-5 font-mono space-y-3" style="font-size: clamp(0.6875rem, 0.65rem + 0.1vw, 0.8125rem); line-height: 1.8;">
          <div>
            <span class="text-accent">⊕</span><span class="text-text-bright">F1:42</span> <span class="text-muted">param(timeout:Duration)</span>
          </div>
          <div class="text-muted/50" style="font-size: 0.7em; padding-left: 1rem;">added parameter</div>

          <div class="term-divider"></div>

          <div>
            <span class="text-danger">⊖</span><span class="text-text-bright">F1:10-15</span>
          </div>
          <div class="text-muted/50" style="font-size: 0.7em; padding-left: 1rem;">removed lines</div>

          <div class="term-divider"></div>

          <div>
            <span class="text-accent-2">∆</span><span class="text-text-bright">F1:42</span> <span class="text-muted">validate_token → verify_jwt</span>
          </div>
          <div class="text-muted/50" style="font-size: 0.7em; padding-left: 1rem;">renamed / refactored</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="terminal-chrome">
        <div class="terminal-header flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2.5">
          <span class="terminal-dot bg-[#ff5f57]"></span>
          <span class="terminal-dot bg-[#febc2e]"></span>
          <span class="terminal-dot bg-[#28c840]"></span>
          <span class="ml-3 text-xs text-muted font-mono">Status Notation</span>
        </div>
        <div class="terminal-body px-5 py-5 font-mono space-y-3" style="font-size: clamp(0.6875rem, 0.65rem + 0.1vw, 0.8125rem); line-height: 1.8;">
          <div>
            <span class="text-accent-3">ctx_read</span><span class="text-muted">(F1)</span>
            <span class="text-muted"> → </span>
            <span class="text-text-bright">808L</span>
            <span class="text-muted"> cached </span>
            <span class="text-accent">✓</span>
          </div>
          <div class="text-muted/50" style="font-size: 0.7em; padding-left: 1rem;">file read — cached, 808 lines</div>

          <div class="term-divider"></div>

          <div>
            <span class="text-accent-3">cargo test</span>
            <span class="text-muted"> → </span>
            <span class="text-accent">82 passed</span>
            <span class="text-muted"> </span>
            <span class="text-accent">✓</span>
            <span class="text-muted"> 0 failed</span>
          </div>
          <div class="text-muted/50" style="font-size: 0.7em; padding-left: 1rem;">test run — all green</div>

          <div class="term-divider"></div>

          <div>
            <span class="text-danger">ERR</span>
            <span class="text-text-bright"> F3:91</span>
            <span class="text-muted"> — missing return type</span>
          </div>
          <div class="text-muted/50" style="font-size: 0.7em; padding-left: 1rem;">error report — file, line, summary</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="section-divider content-grid"></div>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
     RESPONSE RULES
     ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="section-y">
  <div class="content-grid">
    <p class="fluid-label text-muted animate-entrance" style="margin-bottom: clamp(1rem, 0.75rem + 0.5vw, 1.5rem);">
      Rules
    </p>
    <h2 class="font-display fluid-h2 font-bold text-text-bright animate-entrance stagger-1" style="margin-bottom: clamp(1.25rem, 1rem + 0.5vw, 2rem);">
      Response rules.
    </h2>
    <p class="text-muted fluid-body animate-entrance stagger-2" style="margin-bottom: clamp(3rem, 2rem + 3vw, 6rem); max-width: 44rem;">
      TDD enforces six rules that the AI follows in every response. These rules compound — each one reduces token count while preserving the information the developer actually needs.
    </p>

    <div class="tdd-rules-list animate-entrance stagger-3">
      <div class="tdd-rule-item card">
        <span class="tdd-rule-number font-display text-accent-3">1</span>
        <div>
          <p class="text-text-bright font-medium fluid-body" style="margin-bottom: 0.25rem;">Drop all filler</p>
          <p class="text-muted fluid-sm">Remove articles (a, the, an), filler words, and pleasantries. No "I've successfully..." or "Let me help you with..."</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tdd-rule-item card">
        <span class="tdd-rule-number font-display text-accent-3">2</span>
        <div>
          <p class="text-text-bright font-medium fluid-body" style="margin-bottom: 0.25rem;">File references by ID only</p>
          <p class="text-muted fluid-sm">Reference files by Fn refs (F1, F2, F3), never full paths. Short IDs persist across the session.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tdd-rule-item card">
        <span class="tdd-rule-number font-display text-accent-3">3</span>
        <div>
          <p class="text-text-bright font-medium fluid-body" style="margin-bottom: 0.25rem;">Diff lines only</p>
          <p class="text-muted fluid-sm">For code changes, show only the changed lines — not the full file. Use change notation with symbols.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tdd-rule-item card">
        <span class="tdd-rule-number font-display text-accent-3">4</span>
        <div>
          <p class="text-text-bright font-medium fluid-body" style="margin-bottom: 0.25rem;">Show the solution</p>
          <p class="text-muted fluid-sm">No explanations unless asked. Execute first, report concisely. The code is the explanation.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tdd-rule-item card">
        <span class="tdd-rule-number font-display text-accent-3">5</span>
        <div>
          <p class="text-text-bright font-medium fluid-body" style="margin-bottom: 0.25rem;">Tabular format</p>
          <p class="text-muted fluid-sm">Use tables for structured data. Denser than prose, faster to scan, fewer tokens to express relationships.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tdd-rule-item card">
        <span class="tdd-rule-number font-display text-accent-3">6</span>
        <div>
          <p class="text-text-bright font-medium fluid-body" style="margin-bottom: 0.25rem;">Standard abbreviations</p>
          <p class="text-muted fluid-sm font-mono" style="letter-spacing: 0.02em;">fn, cfg, impl, deps, req, res, ctx, err, ok, ret, arg, val, ty, mod</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="section-divider content-grid"></div>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
     BEFORE AND AFTER
     ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="section-y">
  <div class="content-grid">
    <p class="fluid-label text-muted animate-entrance" style="margin-bottom: clamp(1rem, 0.75rem + 0.5vw, 1.5rem);">
      Comparison
    </p>
    <h2 class="font-display fluid-h2 font-bold text-text-bright animate-entrance stagger-1" style="margin-bottom: clamp(1.25rem, 1rem + 0.5vw, 2rem);">
      Before and after.
    </h2>
    <p class="text-muted fluid-body animate-entrance stagger-2" style="margin-bottom: clamp(3rem, 2rem + 3vw, 6rem); max-width: 44rem;">
      The same information, expressed in standard prose versus TDD. The dense version conveys identical meaning in 71% fewer tokens.
    </p>

    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 animate-entrance stagger-3" style="gap: clamp(1rem, 0.75rem + 0.75vw, 1.5rem); margin-bottom: clamp(2rem, 1.5rem + 1vw, 3rem);">
      <div class="terminal-chrome">
        <div class="terminal-header flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2.5">
          <span class="terminal-dot bg-[#ff5f57]"></span>
          <span class="terminal-dot bg-[#febc2e]"></span>
          <span class="terminal-dot bg-[#28c840]"></span>
          <span class="ml-3 text-xs text-muted font-mono">Without TDD &mdash; 42 tokens</span>
        </div>
        <div class="terminal-body px-5 py-5 font-mono" style="font-size: clamp(0.6875rem, 0.65rem + 0.1vw, 0.8125rem); line-height: 1.8;">
          <p class="text-muted" style="word-break: break-word;">"I've successfully read the auth.ts file and found that the validateToken function on line 42 has a bug where it compares UTC timestamps against local timestamps."</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="terminal-chrome tdd-highlight-terminal">
        <div class="terminal-header flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2.5">
          <span class="terminal-dot bg-[#ff5f57]"></span>
          <span class="terminal-dot bg-[#febc2e]"></span>
          <span class="terminal-dot bg-[#28c840]"></span>
          <span class="ml-3 text-xs text-accent-3 font-mono">With TDD &mdash; 12 tokens</span>
        </div>
        <div class="terminal-body px-5 py-5 font-mono" style="font-size: clamp(0.6875rem, 0.65rem + 0.1vw, 0.8125rem); line-height: 1.8;">
          <div><span class="text-accent-3">ctx_read(F1)</span> <span class="text-muted">→</span> <span class="text-text-bright">342L</span> <span class="text-muted">cached</span> <span class="text-accent">✓</span></div>
          <div><span class="text-danger">ERR</span> <span class="text-text-bright">F1:42</span> <span class="text-muted">— UTC vs local timestamp</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="terminal-chrome animate-entrance stagger-4" style="max-width: 28rem;">
      <div class="terminal-header flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2.5">
        <span class="terminal-dot bg-[#ff5f57]"></span>
        <span class="terminal-dot bg-[#febc2e]"></span>
        <span class="terminal-dot bg-[#28c840]"></span>
        <span class="ml-3 text-xs text-muted font-mono">&#167;MAP output</span>
      </div>
      <div class="terminal-body px-5 py-5 font-mono" style="font-size: clamp(0.6875rem, 0.65rem + 0.1vw, 0.8125rem); line-height: 1.8;">
        <div>
          <span class="text-text-bright">A1</span><span class="text-muted">=AuthService</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;
          <span class="text-text-bright">V1</span><span class="text-muted">=validateToken</span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <span class="text-text-bright">S1</span><span class="text-muted">=SessionStore</span>&nbsp;
          <span class="text-text-bright">R1</span><span class="text-muted">=refreshToken</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="section-divider content-grid"></div>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
     FILE REFERENCE SYSTEM
     ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="section-y">
  <div class="content-grid">
    <p class="fluid-label text-muted animate-entrance" style="margin-bottom: clamp(1rem, 0.75rem + 0.5vw, 1.5rem);">
      File References
    </p>
    <h2 class="font-display fluid-h2 font-bold text-text-bright animate-entrance stagger-1" style="margin-bottom: clamp(1.25rem, 1rem + 0.5vw, 2rem);">
      Short IDs, persistent context.
    </h2>
    <p class="text-muted fluid-body animate-entrance stagger-2" style="margin-bottom: clamp(3rem, 2rem + 3vw, 6rem); max-width: 44rem;">
      Every file the AI reads gets a short identifier that persists across the entire session. Combined with session caching, re-reads cost a fraction of the original read.
    </p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 animate-entrance stagger-3" style="gap: clamp(1px, 0.1vw, 1px);">
      <div class="tdd-ref-card card">
        <div class="tdd-ref-id font-display text-accent-3">F1, F2, F3</div>
        <p class="text-muted fluid-sm">Files get short IDs on first read. No more repeating full paths.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tdd-ref-card card">
        <div class="tdd-ref-id font-display text-accent-3">Session</div>
        <p class="text-muted fluid-sm">IDs persist across the entire session. F1 always refers to the same file.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tdd-ref-card card">
        <div class="tdd-ref-id font-display text-accent">~13 tok</div>
        <p class="text-muted fluid-sm">Re-reads cost approximately 13 tokens thanks to session caching.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tdd-ref-card card">
        <div class="tdd-ref-id font-display text-accent-2">&#167;MAP</div>
        <p class="text-muted fluid-sm">Maps long identifiers to short IDs. AuthService becomes A1.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
